FBIS4-54009 "dreas101__a94016" FBIS-EAS-94-101-A Daily Report 19 May 1994 ANNEX Japan Komeito Official on Impact of Kaishin Dissolution Komeito Official on Impact of Kaishin Dissolution OW2005044894 Tokyo NIHON KEIZAI SHIMBUN in Japanese 19 May 94 Morning Edition p 2--FOR OFFICIAL USE ONLY OW2005044894 Tokyo NIHON KEIZAI SHIMBUN Japanese BFN [Text] The ruling Democratic Socialist Party [DSP] and the ruling New Japan Party are advocating breaking up the unified parliamentary group "Kaishin" [Innovation]. Commenting on the two ruling parties' move at an 18 May meeting of Komeito legislators, Komeito Secretary General Yuichi Ichikawa said: "If the two ruling parties, which formed "Kaishin," have altered their policies, their leadership cannot escape the responsibility." In this way, he indicated that if the "Kaishin" is dissolved, Keigo Ouchi, chairman of the DSP; Morihiro Hosokawa, representative of the Japan New Party; and Ichiro Ozawa, secretary general of Shinseito [Japan Renewal Party], would need to step down.
